
[1]chian

   CHIAN, a. Pertaining to Chios, an isle in the Levant.

   Chian earth, a medicinal, dense, compact kind of earth, from Chios,
   used anciently as an astringent, and a cosmetic.

   Chian turpentine, or Cyprus turpentine, is procured from the Pistacia
   Terebinthus. It is of the consistence of honey, clear and of a
   yellowish white.
